[2025-12-27 16:31:47] ðŸ’¡ AI DECISION: One potential web UI improvement for these HTML files is to add a loading animation when the pages are loading. This can be achieved by adding a CSS animation and some JavaScript code to trigger the animation.

**HTML Changes:**

Add a `<div>` element with a class of `loading` to the `<body>` of both `index.html` and `games.html` files:

```html
<body class="dark-theme" id="loading-page">
  <!-- existing content -->
</body>
```

**CSS Changes:**

Add CSS to `style.css` to style the loading animation:

```css
#loading-page .loading {
  position: fixed;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  z-index: 100;
  width: 100px;
  height: 100px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background-color: #000;
  animation: loading-animation 2s infinite;
}

#loading-page.hide-loading {
  animation: none;
}

@keyframes loading-animation {
  0% {
    transform: scale(0.5);
  }
  50% {
    transform: scale(1);
  }
  100% {
    transform: scale(0.5);
  }
}
```

**JavaScript Changes:**

Add JavaScript to both `index.html` and `games.html` files to trigger the loading animation and hide it when the page is fully loaded:

```javascript
<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
    const loadingElement = document.getElementById("loading-page");
    loadingElement.classList.add("hide-loading");
  });
</script>
```

